obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (42434)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00007_195556_1517807319389&sectionId=42434&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00007_195556_1517807319389
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Manipur (Courts) Act,`
  line 1955.
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of the ^1`
  line `[Union territory of Manipur].`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^2`
  line `as the Chief Commissioner may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by A.O. (No. 3), 1956 for "State of Manipur" (w.e.f. 1-3-1956).`
  line
  line `2. 1st March, 1956, vide Chief Commissioner, Manipur's notification No. J/12/1956, dated 3rd February, 1956.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (42435)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by A.O. (No. 3), 1956 for "State of Manipur" (w.e.f. 1-3-1956).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00007_195556_1517807319389&sectionId=42435&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00007_195556_1517807319389
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,`
  line
  line `(i) "Chief Commissioner" means the Chief Commissioner of Manipur;`
  line
  line `(ii) "civil suit" includes every suit of a civil nature not expressly or impliedly classed otherwise by`
  line `any law for the time being in force;`
  line
  line `(iii) "district court" means the court of the district judge and includes the court of the additional`
  line `district judge;`
  line
  line `(iv) "hill areas" mean such areas in the hill tracts of the ^1`
  line `[Union territory of Manipur] as the Chief`
  line `Commissioner may, by notification in the Official Gazette, declare to be hill areas;`
  line
  line `(v) "small cause suit" means a suit of the nature cognizable by a court of small causes under the`
  line `Provincial Small Cause Courts Act, 1887(9 of 1887);`
  line
  line `(vi) "value" in relation to a suit means the amount or value of the subject-matter of the suit.`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (42436)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Establishment of the Court of the Judicial Commissioner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by A.O. (No. 3), 1956 for "State of Manipur" (w.e.f. 1-3-1956).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00007_195556_1517807319389&sectionId=42436&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00007_195556_1517807319389
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `There shall be established for the`
  line ^1
  line `[Union territory of Manipur] a court to be known as the Court of the Judicial Commissioner for Manipur`
  line `which shall consist of the Judicial Commissioner and the Additional Judicial Commissioner, if any.`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (42437)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Appointment of Judicial Commissioner and Additional Judicial Commissioner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00007_195556_1517807319389&sectionId=42437&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00007_195556_1517807319389
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) The`
  line `Judicial Commissioner and the Additional Judicial Commissioner, if any, shall be appointed by, and shall`
  line `hold office during the pleasure of, the President.`
  line
  line `(2) A person shall not be appointed as Judicial Commissioner or Additional Judicial Commissioner`
  line `unless he is qualified to be appointed as a Judge of a High Court under clause (2) of article 217 of the`
  line `Constitution or unless he was, immediately before the commencement of this Act, the Judicial`
  line `Commissioner of Manipur.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (42438)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Casual vacancy in the office of the Judicial Commissioner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00007_195556_1517807319389&sectionId=42438&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00007_195556_1517807319389
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `On the occurrence of a vacancy in`
  line `the office of the Judicial Commissioner, the Additional Judicial Commissioner, if any, or if there is no`
  line `Additional Judicial Commissioner, the senior-most district judge shall, pending the appointment of the`
  line `Judicial Commissioner, act as the Judicial Commissioner.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (42439)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Rank, precedence and responsibility of Judicial Commissioner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00007_195556_1517807319389&sectionId=42439&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00007_195556_1517807319389
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `The Judicial Commissioner`
  line `shall have rank and precedence before the Additional Judicial Commissioner and shall be responsible for`
  line `the administration of, and generally for the distribution of business in, the Court of the Judicial`
  line Commissioner.
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (42440)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Exercising of jurisdiction by Judicial Commissioner and Additional Judicial Commissioner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00007_195556_1517807319389&sectionId=42440&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00007_195556_1517807319389
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `Subject to such orders as the Judicial Commissioner may make as regards the distribution of business`
  line `between himself and the Additional Judicial Commissioner, the jurisdiction of the Court of the Judicial`
  line `Commissioner may be exercised by the Judicial Commissioner or by the Additional Judicial`
  line Commissioner.
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (42441)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Civil and criminal jurisdiction of the Court of the Judicial Commissioner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by A.O. (No. 3), 1956 for "State of Manipur" (w.e.f. 1-3-1956).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00007_195556_1517807319389&sectionId=42441&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00007_195556_1517807319389
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `Save as otherwise`
  line `provided by this Act or any other law for the time being in force, the Court of the Judicial Commissioner`
  line `shall, with reference to any civil or criminal proceeding under any law for the time being in force in the`
  line ^1
  line `[Union territory of Manipur], be the highest court of appeal, revision or reference.`
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (42442)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Registrar and ministerial officers of the Court of the Judicial Commissioner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00007_195556_1517807319389&sectionId=42442&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00007_195556_1517807319389
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Judicial`
  line `Commissioner may appoint a Registrar and such other ministerial officers as may be necessary for the`
  line `administration of justice by the Court of the Judicial Commissioner and for the exercise of the powers and`
  line `the performance of the duties conferred or imposed on the Court by or under this Act or any other law for`
  line `the time being in force.`
  line
  line `(2) The Judicial Commissioner may make rules for delegating to the Registrar such powers and duties`
  line `of a judicial, quasi-judicial or non-judicial nature as he thinks fit; and the ministerial officers shall exercise`
  line `such powers and perform such duties of a quasi-judicial or non-judicial nature as the Judicial`
  line `Commissioner may direct.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (42443)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Superintendence and control of subordinate court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by A.O. (No. 3), 1956 for "State of Manipur" (w.e.f. 1-3-1956).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00007_195556_1517807319389&sectionId=42443&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00007_195556_1517807319389
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) The general superintendence and`
  line `control of all courts in the ^1`
  line `[Union territory of Manipur] shall vest in, and all such courts shall be`
  line `subordinate to, the Court of the Judicial Commissioner.`
  line
  line `(2) In exercise of the powers of general superintendence and control vested in it but without prejudice`
  line `to the generality of such powers, the Court of the Judicial Commissioner may,—`
  line
  line `(a) call for returns from such courts;`
  line
  line `(b) direct the transfer of any suit, proceeding, case or appeal from any subordinate court to any`
  line `other court of equal or superior jurisdiction;`
  line
  line `(c) make rules and issue general directions and prescribe forms for regulating practice and`
  line `procedure of subordinate courts;`
  line
  line `(d) prescribe forms in which books, entries and accounts shall be kept by the officers of any such`
  line courts.
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (42444)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Registers, books, accounts and statements to be kept by the Judicial Commissioner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00007_195556_1517807319389&sectionId=42444&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00007_195556_1517807319389
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) The`
  line `Court of the Judicial Commissioner shall keep such registers, books and accounts as may be necessary for`
  line `the transaction of the business of the Court and shall forward to the Chief Commissioner such of these`
  line `registers, books and accounts and such statements of the work done in the Court as may, from time to time,`
  line `be required by the Chief Commissioner.`
  line
  line `(2) The Court of the Judicial Commissioner shall also comply with such requisitions as may be made`
  line `by the Central Government or the Chief Commissioner for certified copies of, or extracts from, the records`
  line `of the Court of the Judicial Commissioner or any court subordinate thereto.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (42445)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Procedure of the Court of the Judicial Commissioner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00007_195556_1517807319389&sectionId=42445&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00007_195556_1517807319389
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in`
  line `the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), or the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1898 (5 of 1898), the`
  line `Court of the Judicial Commissioner shall record evidence and judgments in such manner and prescribe such forms to be used in proceedings before it, as it may direct by rules made by it with the sanction of the`
  line `Chief Commissioner.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (42446)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Admission and removal of advocates, vakils and pleaders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by A.O. (No. 3), 1956 for "State of Manipur" (w.e.f. 1-3-1956).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00007_195556_1517807319389&sectionId=42446&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00007_195556_1517807319389
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Court of the Judicial`
  line `Commissioner may, subject to such rules as it may with the sanction of the Chief Commissioner make,`
  line `admit proper persons to be advocates, vakils and pleaders in any court in the ^1`
  line `[Union territory of Manipur]`
  line `and may remove or suspend from practice on reasonable cause any person so admitted and may authorize`
  line `such advocates, vakils and pleaders to plead or to act or to plead and act for parties and accused persons.`
  line
  line `(2) No person other than an advocate, vakil or pleader shall be allowed to plead or to act for parties`
  line `and accused persons except that any party may appear, plead or act on his own behalf or on behalf of`
  line `another party if so authorized.`
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (42447)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Court of the Judicial Commissioner to be a court of record.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00007_195556_1517807319389&sectionId=42447&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00007_195556_1517807319389
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `The Court of the Judicial`
  line `Commissioner shall be a court of record and shall have all powers of such court including the power to`
  line `punish for contempt of itself.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (42448)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Place of sitting of the Court of the Judicial Commissioner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00007_195556_1517807319389&sectionId=42448&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00007_195556_1517807319389
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `The Court of the Judicial`
  line `Commissioner shall sit at Imphal or at such other place or places, if any, as the Judicial Commissioner`
  line `may, with the approval of the Chief Commissioner, from time to time, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (42449)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Classes of subordinate civil courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes `. Subs. by A.O. (No. 3), 1956 for "State of Manipur" (w.e.f. 1-3-1956).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00007_195556_1517807319389&sectionId=42449&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00007_195556_1517807319389
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `In addition to the Court of the Judicial Commissioner and`
  line `the courts of small causes established under the Provincial Small Cause Courts Act, 1887 (IX of 1887),`
  line `and the courts established under any other law for the time being in force, there shall be the following`
  line `classes of civil courts in the ^1`
  line `[Union territory of Manipur], namely:—`
  line
  line `(i) the district court;`
  line
  line `(ii) the court of a subordinate judge;`
  line
  line `(iii) the court of a munsiff:`
  line
  line `Provided that the court of a subordinate judge shall be established only with effect from such date as`
  line `the Chief Commissioner may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify.`
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (42450)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Civil districts and district judges.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by A.O. (No. 3), 1956 for "State of Manipur" (w.e.f. 1-3-1956).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00007_195556_1517807319389&sectionId=42450&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00007_195556_1517807319389
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purposes of this Chapter, the Chief Commissioner`
  line `may, by notification in the Official Gazette, divide the ^1`
  line `[Union territory of Manipur] into civil districts and`
  line `sub-divisions, alter the limits or the number of these districts and sub-divisions and determine the`
  line `headquarters of each district and sub-division.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chief Commissioner shall, after consultation with the Judicial Commissioner, appoint as many`
  line `persons as he thinks necessary to be district judges and shall post one of these persons to each district as`
  line `district judge of that district:`
  line
  line `Provided that the same person may, if the Chief Commissioner thinks fit, be appointed to be district`
  line `judge of two or more districts.`
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (42451)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Additional district judges.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00007_195556_1517807319389&sectionId=42451&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00007_195556_1517807319389
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) When the business pending before the court of a district judge`
  line `requires the aid of an additional district judge for its speedy disposal, the Chief Commissioner may, after`
  line `consultation with the Judicial Commissioner, appoint such number of additional district judges as may be`
  line necessary.
  line
  line `(2) The additional district judges so appointed shall discharge any of the functions of a district judge`
  line `which the district Judge may assign to them and in the discharge of those functions they shall exercise the`
  line `same powers as the district judge.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (42452)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Subordinate judges and munsiffs.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00007_195556_1517807319389&sectionId=42452&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00007_195556_1517807319389
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chief Commissioner may, after consultation with the`
  line `Judicial Commissioner, fix the number of subordinate judges and munsiffs to be appointed and if there is a`
  line `vacancy in that number, may, subject to the rules, if any, made under sub-section (2), appoint such person`
  line `as is nominated by the Judicial Commissioner to the vacancy.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chief Commissioner may, after consultation with the Judicial Commissioner, make rules as to`
  line `the qualifications of persons to be appointed as subordinate judges and munsiffs.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (42453)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `District court to be principal civil court of original jurisdiction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00007_195556_1517807319389&sectionId=42453&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00007_195556_1517807319389
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `The district court shall be`
  line `the principal civil court of original jurisdiction in the district.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (42454)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Original jurisdiction of district courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00007_195556_1517807319389&sectionId=42454&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00007_195556_1517807319389
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `Save as otherwise provided by any other law for the`
  line `time being in force, the district court, shall, subject to the provisions of section 15 of the Code of Civil`
  line `Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), have original jurisdiction in all civil suits without limit as regards the value.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (42455)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Original jurisdiction of courts of subordinate judges and munsiffs.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00007_195556_1517807319389&sectionId=42455&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00007_195556_1517807319389
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `The jurisdiction in`
  line `original civil suits as regards the value to be exercised by a subordinate judge or a munsiff shall be`
  line `determined by the Chief Commissioner in such manner as he thinks fit, after consultation with the Judicial`
  line `Commissioner:`
  line
  line `Provided that in no case shall the jurisdiction of a munsiffbe without limit.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (42456)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Local limits of the jurisdiction of courts of subordinate judges and munsiffs.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00007_195556_1517807319389&sectionId=42456&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00007_195556_1517807319389
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) The local`
  line `limits of the jurisdiction of the court of a subordinate judge or a munsiff shall be such as the Chief`
  line `Commissioner may, by notification in the Official Gazette, define.`
  line
  line `(2) When the Chief Commissioner posts a subordinate judge to a district, the local limits of the district`
  line `shall, in the absence of any direction to the contrary, be the local limits of his jurisdiction.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (42457)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Small causes jurisdiction of subordinate judges and munsiffs.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00007_195556_1517807319389&sectionId=42457&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00007_195556_1517807319389
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `The Judicial Commissioner`
  line `may, by notification in the Official Gazette, confer within such local limits as he thinks fit, upon any`
  line `district judge, subordinate judge or munsiff, the jurisdiction of a judge of the court of small causes under`
  line `the Provincial Small Cause Courts Act, 1887 (9 of 1887), for the trial of suits of the nature cognizable by`
  line `such courts upto such value not exceeding five hundred rupees, as he thinks fit and may withdraw any`
  line `jurisdiction so conferred.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (42480)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Exercise by subordinate judges and munsiffs of jurisdiction of district courts in certain proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00007_195556_1517807319389&sectionId=42480&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00007_195556_1517807319389
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Judicial Commissioner may, by general or special order, authorize any subordinate`
  line `judge or munsiff to take cognizance of, or any district judge to transfer to a subordinate judge or a munsiff`
  line `under his administrative control, any proceeding or class of proceedings specified in such order, under—`
  line
  line `(a) the Indian Succession Act, 1925 (39 1925); or`
  line
  line `(b) the Guardians and Wards Act, 1890 (8 of 1890); or`
  line
  line `(c) the Provincial Insolvency Act, 1920 (5 of 1920).`
  line
  line `(2) The district judge may withdraw any such proceeding taken cognizance of by, or transferred to, a`
  line `subordinate judge or a munsiff and may either himself dispose of them or transfer it for disposal to any`
  line `other competent court under his administrative control.`
  line
  line `(3) Proceedings taken cognizance of by, or transferred to, a subordinate judge or a munsiff under this`
  line `section shall be disposed of by him subject to the rules applicable to like proceedings when disposed of by`
  line `the district judge:`
  line
  line `Provided that an appeal from an order of the munsiff in any such proceedings shall lie to the district`
  line judge.
  line
  line `(4) An appeal from the order of the district judge on appeal from the order of a munsiff under this`
  line `section shall lie to the Court of the Judicial Commissioner if a further appeal from the order of the district`
  line `judge is allowed by the law for the time being in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (42459)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Place of sittings of courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00007_195556_1517807319389&sectionId=42459&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00007_195556_1517807319389
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chief Commissioner may, by order, fix a place or places at`
  line `which any court constituted under this Chapter is to be held.`
  line
  line `(2) The place or places so fixed may be beyond the local limits of the jurisdiction of the court.`
  line
  line `(3) Save as otherwise provided by an order under this section, a court constituted under this Act may`
  line `be held at any place within the local limits of its jurisdiction.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (42460)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Administrative control of courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00007_195556_1517807319389&sectionId=42460&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00007_195556_1517807319389
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the general superintendence and control of the`
  line `Court of the Judicial Commissioner, the district judge shall have administrative control over all the civil`
  line `courts under this Chapter within the local limits of his jurisdiction.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (42461)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `District Judge's power to distribute business.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00007_195556_1517807319389&sectionId=42461&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00007_195556_1517807319389
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code`
  line `of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), the district judge may, by written order, direct that any business`
  line `cognizable by his court and the courts under his control shall be distributed among such courts, and in such`
  line `manner, as he thinks fit:`
  line
  line `Provided that no direction issued under this section shall empower any court to exercise any power and`
  line `deal with any business beyond the limits of its jurisdiction.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (42462)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Seals of courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00007_195556_1517807319389&sectionId=42462&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00007_195556_1517807319389
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `Every court under this Chapter shall use a seal of such form and dimension as`
  line `are prescribed by the Chief Commissioner.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (42463)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Ministerial officers of the courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00007_195556_1517807319389&sectionId=42463&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00007_195556_1517807319389
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `(1) Ministerial officers of the district court shall be appointed`
  line `by the district judge.`
  line
  line `(2) Ministerial officers of civil courts under the administrative control of the district judge shall be`
  line `appointed by the district judge.`
  line
  line `(3) Every appointment under this section shall be subject to such rules as the Judicial Commissioner`
  line `may make in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(4) Any order passed by the district judge under this section shall be liable to be reversed or modified`
  line `by the Judicial Commissioner.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (42464)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Delegation of powers of district judges and district courts in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00007_195556_1517807319389&sectionId=42464&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00007_195556_1517807319389
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `The district judge`
  line `may, with the previous sanction of the Judicial Commissioner, delegate to the judge of any court under his`
  line `administrative control all or any of the powers conferred on a district judge by section 27 and section 28 of`
  line `this Act and on a district court by section 24 of the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), to be`
  line `exercised by the judge in any specified portion of the district subject to the control of the district judge.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (42465)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Appeals from original decrees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00007_195556_1517807319389&sectionId=42465&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00007_195556_1517807319389
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `Save as otherwise provided by any law for the time being in`
  line `force, appeals from decrees or orders of courts exercising original jurisdiction shall lie as follows:—`
  line
  line `(a) from a decree or order of a munsiff in any suit and of a subordinate judge in a suit the value of`
  line `which does not exceed five thousand rupees, to the court of the district judge; and`
  line
  line `(b) in all other cases, to the court of the Judicial Commissioner.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (42466)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Appeals from appellate decrees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00007_195556_1517807319389&sectionId=42466&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00007_195556_1517807319389
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `A second appeal shall lie to the court of the Judicial`
  line `Commissioner from an appellate decree or order of a district court on any ground on which a second`
  line `appeal lies under section 100 of the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908).`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (42467)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Revisional powers of the Court of the Judicial Commissioner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00007_195556_1517807319389&sectionId=42467&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00007_195556_1517807319389
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `In addition to the powers`
  line `conferred by section 115 of the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), the Court of the Judicial`
  line `Commissioner may, on application made to it, call for the record of any case which has been decided by a`
  line `civil court subordinate to it and in which no appeal lies to it and if the Court of the Judicial Commissioner`
  line `is of opinion that there is an important question of law or custom and the question requires further`
  line `consideration, the Court of the Judicial Commissioner may make such order in the case as it thinks fit:`
  line
  line `Provided that—`
  line
  line `(i) no application shall be admitted after the expiration of ninety days from the date of the decision`
  line `in respect of which the application is made unless the applicant satisfies the Court of the Judicial`
  line `Commissioner that he had sufficient cause for not making application within that period;`
  line
  line `(ii) on any such application the Court of the Judicial Commissioner shall not revise the decision of`
  line `the court below except in so far as such decision involves a question of law or custom in respect of`
  line `which the application has been admitted; and`
  line
  line `(iii) when any such application has been admitted the Court of the Judicial Commissioner shall,`
  line `subject to clause (ii) of this proviso, treat the matter of the application as if it were an appeal.`
  line
  line `Explanation 1.—The question of procedure is not a question of law or custom within the meaning`
  line `of this section.`
  line
  line `Explanation 2.—In computing the period of limitation mentioned in clause (i) of this proviso and`
  line `in all other respects not herein specified, the period of limitation of the application shall be governed`
  line `by the provisions of the Indian Limitation Act, 1908 (5 of 1908).`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (42468)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Court fees payable on applications for revision.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00007_195556_1517807319389&sectionId=42468&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00007_195556_1517807319389
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `(1) The court fees payable on applications to`
  line `the Court of the Judicial Commissioner for the exercise of its jurisdiction under section 34 shall be such as`
  line `are prescribed by the Chief Commissioner in consultation with the Judicial Commissioner.`
  line
  line `(2) If the Court of the Judicial Commissioner, on an application in respect of which the court fee`
  line `payable under sub-section (1) has been paid, sets aside or modifies a decree or order of the court below or`
  line `remands the case for further decision, the Court of the Judicial Commissioner may grant to the applicant a`
  line `certificate authorising him to receive back from the Collector of the district in which the court below is`
  line `situated or from such other officer as the Chief Commissioner may authorise by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, the full amount of such court fee or such part thereof as the Court of the Judicial Commissioner`
  line `having regard to the circumstances of the case may think fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (42469)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `Temporary vacancy in the office of district judge.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00007_195556_1517807319389&sectionId=42469&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00007_195556_1517807319389
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `In the event of death of a district judge or of`
  line `his being prevented from performing his duties by illness or other cause or of his absence from the civil`
  line `district on leave, the additional district judge, if any, in the district or where there is no additional district`
  line `judge, the senior-most subordinate judge, or as the case may be, the senior-most munsiff in the district`
  line `shall assume charge of the district court without interruption of his ordinary jurisdiction and being so in`
  line `charge shall perform the duties of the district judge with respect to the filing of suits and appeals, receiving`
  line `pleadings, execution of processes, return of writs and the like, and shall be designated as the additional`
  line `district judge or the subordinate judge or the munsiff, as the case may be, in charge of the district and shall`
  line `continue in such charge until the office of the district judge has been resumed by him or assumed by an`
  line `officer duly appointed thereto.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (42470)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title `Delegation of powers of district judges.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00007_195556_1517807319389&sectionId=42470&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00007_195556_1517807319389
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `Any district judge leaving headquarters and proceeding`
  line `on duty to any place in the district may delegate to the additional district judge, if any, or where there is no`
  line `such additional district judge, to a subordinate judge or, as the case may be, to a munsiff at the`
  line `headquarters, the power of performing such duties enumerated in section 36 as may be emergent and such`
  line `officer shall be designated as the additional district judge or the subordinate judge or the munsiff, as the`
  line `case may be, in charge of the headquarter.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (42471)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title `Temporary vacancy in the office of a subordinate judge or munsiff.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00007_195556_1517807319389&sectionId=42471&sectionno=38&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00007_195556_1517807319389
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `In the event of death,`
  line `suspension or temporary absence of a subordinate-judge or a munsiff, the district judge may empower any`
  line `other subordinate judge or munsiff of the same civil district to continue the duties of the vacated court of`
  line `the subordinate judge or munsiff either at the place of such court or of his own court but in every such case`
  line `the register and record of the court shall be kept distinct.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (42481)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 39
  title `Power to confer powers of civil courts on officers in Hill Areas and procedure before the courts of such officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00007_195556_1517807319389&sectionId=42481&sectionno=39&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00007_195556_1517807319389
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chief Commissioner after consultation with the Judicial Commissioner may, by notification in the Official Gazette, invest, by name or in virtue of office, any officer in the hill`
  line `areas with the powers of any civil court under this Act and upon such investiture the provisions of this Act`
  line `shall, so far as they can be made applicable, apply to him as if he were a judge of the court with the powers`
  line `of which he is invested.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the place at which the court of an officer invested with powers under sub-section (1) is to be`
  line `held, has not been fixed under section 26, the court may be held at any place within the local limits of its`
  line jurisdiction.
  line
  line `(3) The Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), shall apply to all suits and proceedings before the`
  line `court of an officer invested with powers under sub-section (1) subject to the following exceptions,`
  line `namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) a defendant in a suit may, instead of filing a written statement, make an oral statement of his`
  line `defence which shall be recorded by the court;`
  line
  line `(b) all applications by parties in any suit or proceeding may be made orally before the court;`
  line
  line `(c) no appearance, application or act in or to the court, required or authorised by law to be made or`
  line `done by a party in such court shall be made or done by a pleader (as defined in the Code of Civil`
  line `Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908)) save with the permission of the court;`
  line
  line `(d) it shall be sufficient for the court to make a memorandum of the substance of the evidence of`
  line `any witness examined by it and it shall not be necessary for the court to take down evidence of any`
  line `witness in writing at length unless the court is, on the application of any party or otherwise, satisfied`
  line `that there is any special reason for so doing.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (42473)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 40
  title `Power of the Judicial Commissioner to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00007_195556_1517807319389&sectionId=42473&sectionno=40&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00007_195556_1517807319389
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `The Court of the Judicial Commissioner`
  line `may make rules consistent with this Act and any other law for the time being in force, providing for all or`
  line `any of the following matters, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) the supervision of all courts subordinate to the Court of the Judicial Commissioner and their`
  line inspection;
  line
  line `(b) the translation of any papers filed in the Court of the Judicial Commissioner and the`
  line `preparation of paper-books for the hearing of appeals and the copying, typing or printing of any such`
  line `papers or translations and the recovery from the persons at whose instance or on whose behalf papers`
  line `are filed, all the expenses thereby incurred;`
  line
  line `(c) the fees to be charged for processes issued by a civil court or by any officer of any such court`
  line `and the fee payable in any suit or proceeding, in any such court by any party to such suit or proceeding`
  line `in respect of the fees of the pleader of any other party to such suit or proceeding;`
  line
  line `(d) the manner in which the proceedings of civil courts shall be kept and recorded, and the manner`
  line `in which paper-books for the hearing shall be prepared and the granting of copies;`
  line
  line `(e) the various matters relating to the officers of the court;`
  line
  line `(f) the persons to be, permitted to act as petition-writers in the court subordinate thereto or act as`
  line `pleaders' clerks;`
  line
  line `(g) the issue of licences to persons referred to in clause (f), the conduct of business by them and`
  line `the scale of fees to be charged by them;`
  line
  line `(h) the authority by which breaches of such rules shall be investigated and the penalty which may`
  line `be imposed.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (42474)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 41
  title `Presiding officers of courts not to try suits and cases in which they are interested.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00007_195556_1517807319389&sectionId=42474&sectionno=41&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00007_195556_1517807319389
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `(1) The`
  line `presiding officer of a court shall not try any suit, proceeding or other case, or hear any appeal, to which he`
  line `is a party or in which he is personally interested.`
  line
  line `(2) No presiding officer shall hear an appeal from any judgment, decree, sentence or order passed or`
  line `made by himself.`
  line
  line `(3) Where any such suit, proceeding, case or appeal as is referred to in sub-section (1) or sub-section`
  line `(2) comes before any such officer, he shall transmit forthwith the record of such suit, proceeding, case or`
  line `appeal as the case may be, to the court to which he is immediately subordinate with the report of the`
  line `circumstances attending the reference.`
  line
  line `(4) The superior court may transfer the suit, proceeding, case or appeal either to itself or to any court`
  line `under its administrative control competent to decide it.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (42475)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 42
  title `Certain decisions to be according to custom or personal law.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00007_195556_1517807319389&sectionId=42475&sectionno=42&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00007_195556_1517807319389
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where in any suit or`
  line `proceeding, it is necessary for any court under this Act to decide any question regarding succession,`
  line `inheritance, marriage or caste or any religious usage or institution, any custom (if such there be) having the`
  line `force of law, orany personal law, governing the parties, or the property of the parties to such suit or`
  line `proceeding shall form the rule of decision except in so far as such custom or personal law has, by`
  line `legislative enactment, been altered or abolished.`
  line
  line `(2) In cases not provided for by sub-section (1) or by any other law for the time being in force, the`
  line `court shall decide the suit or proceeding according to justice, equity and good conscience.`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (42476)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 43
  title Holidays.
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00007_195556_1517807319389&sectionId=42476&sectionno=43&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00007_195556_1517807319389
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the approval of the Chief Commissioner, the Judicial Commissioner`
  line `shall prepare a list of days to be observed in each year as closed holidays in the Court of the Judicial`
  line `Commissioner and the civil courts subordinate to that Court.`
  line
  line `(2) The list of holidays shall be published in the Official Gazette.`
  line
  line `(3) A judicial act done by a court on a day specified in the list shall not be invalid by reason only of its`
  line `having been done on that day.`
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (42477)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 44
  title `Pending proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00007_195556_1517807319389&sectionId=42477&sectionno=44&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00007_195556_1517807319389
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any suit, proceeding, case or appeal pending in a court immediately`
  line `before the commencement of this Act shall, upon the commencement of this Act, be deemed to be`
  line `transferred to the court exercising under this Act jurisdiction which corresponds, as far as may be, to the`
  line `jurisdiction of the court in which the suit, proceeding, case or appeal was pending and the court to which`
  line `the suit, proceeding, case or appeal is deemed to be transferred shall proceed to try, hear and determine the`
  line `matter as if it had been pending in that court.`
  line
  line `(2) Any appeal from a judgment, decree, sentence or order passed or made by a court and not appealed`
  line `against before the commencement of this Act shall, after such commencement, lie to the court exercising`
  line `under this Act jurisdiction which corresponds, as far as may be, to the jurisdiction of the court to which`
  line `such appeal would have lain if this Act had not been passed and had not come into force.`
  line
  line `(3) Any judgment, decree, sentence or order passed or made before the commencement of this Act by`
  line `any court shall be deemed for the purpose of execution to have been passed by a court constituted under`
  line `this Act which corresponds, as far as may be, to the court which passed or made the judgment, decree,`
  line `sentence or order as the case may be:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) shall be construed as extending`
  line `period of limitation to which any suit, proceeding, case or appeal may be subject.`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (42478)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 45
  title `Repeals and savings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00007_195556_1517807319389&sectionId=42478&sectionno=45&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00007_195556_1517807319389
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Manipur State Courts Act 1947, as amended by the Manipur State`
  line `Courts (Amendment) Order, 1950, is hereby repealed.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding such repeal, anything done or any action taken (including any appointment or`
  line `delegation made, order, Instrument or direction issued, rule or regulation made under that Act) shall be`
  line `deemed to have been done or taken under the corresponding provisions of this Act and shall continue in`
  line `force accordingly unless and until superseded by anything done or any action taken under the relevant`
  line `provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (42479)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 46
  title `Declaration of the Judicial Commissioner's Court as a High Court for certain purposes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00007_195556_1517807319389&sectionId=42479&sectionno=46&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00007_195556_1517807319389
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `The Court of the Judicial Commissioner established under section 3 is hereby declared to be a High Court`
  line `for the purposes of articles 132, 133 and 134 of the Constitution; and the provisions of the Judicial`
  line `Commissioners' Courts (Declaration as High Courts) Act, 1950 (15 of 1950), shall apply to that Court as`
  line `they apply to a Judicial Commissioner's Court in existence at the commencement of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line
